SEC. 10. Section 16 of Republic Act No. 7306 is hereby amended to read as follows:

ГўВЂВњSEC. 16.

General Program Standards.

ГўВЂВ“ The Board of Directors is mandated to set up a Code of Standards, inclusive of the following aspects:

ГўВЂВњ(a) Presentations of news;

ГўВЂВњ(b) Public Affairs Programs and Commentaries;

ГўВЂВњ(c) Public Service Programs;

ГўВЂВњ(d) Educational Programs;

ГўВЂВњ(e) ChildrenГўВЂВ™s Programs;

ГўВЂВњ(f) Agriculture and Livelihood Programs;

ГўВЂВњ(g) Women and Youth Issues;

ГўВЂВњ(h) Locally-produced and foreign produced programs;

ГўВЂВњ(i) Trade, service and manufacturing industry programs; and

ГўВЂВњ(j) Programs that inspire nationalism.ГўВЂВќ

SEC. 11. Section 17 of Republic Act No. 7306 is hereby amended to read as follows:

ГўВЂВњSEC. 17.

Use of Blocktimers.

ГўВЂВ“ The use of blocktimers shall be allowed but limited to education, sports, tourism, quality entertainment programs, and such programs which promote public interest, subject to quality standards set by the Board of Directors. The Network shall assume solidary liability with each of the individual producers, for the content of all programs shown by blocktimers.ГўВЂВќ
